The paper deals with resource allocation and interference management in wireless networks, which is a common topic in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The use of sparsity-pursuit algorithms suggests a focus on optimization and signal processing, which are also relevant to the Signal and Image Processing (cs.SI) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a unified framework to analyze and compare different strategies, which could fall under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
